Shit, man. I'm still hopeful for seeing FFI or really any other kind of long form story from you, but I understand the frustration of something else being more popular than the other, making it a "what's the point" kinda problem.

I still think there's plenty of readers that would be quick to show their thanks for the story when its completed. Hard giving feedback when the most that can really be said sometimes is "It's good". I'm sorry to hear you feel that way, though.

I really do like the ragtag group you've made and finding a way to keep them all unique and equally likable, and the situation they're all in makes any small victory for them feel rewarding. I understand the issue of some characters getting the spotlight more than others, but that's unfortunately what happens in a group sorta setting, and the only cure for that is just spending more time on the story as a whole. However, I understand you wanting to write other things, but I can also say that all of them feel well-rounded and explored, with the only character I'd wish getting more exploration being Sandra, since she's the one that shied away from interaction the most.

Anyway, call me a brown nosing sap, but reading the story makes me feel good for a lack of a better term. Finding moments of happiness in hard times is something I'm super into, and I never really had a thought while reading through it that kicked me out of that feeling.
